main event: Observers reported seeing multiple unidentified objects over Spooner, Wisconsin in June 1966, with various descriptions across several reports.
interesting points: The objects were observed at different times and durations, generally described as having no sound and exhibiting unusual movements., The reports mention at least two distinct objects, one described as disk-shaped and another as silvery and oblong., Observations included details like the height of the objects (~25 ft) and their speed and maneuverability., Multiple witnesses reported seeing these objects at close range, with some providing sketches of their movements., One report noted the objects illuminated as they moved rapidly across the sky.
witness description: varied, including military personnel and civilians
